1
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:30,729
=My Dear Guardian=

2
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:34,070
=Episode 26=

3
00:01:40,940 --> 00:01:43,190
Are you here looking
for someone of your same kind?

4
00:01:45,210 --> 00:01:46,150
Are you?

5
00:01:50,570 --> 00:01:51,640
What do you think?

6
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:20,800
Zhuo Ran.

7
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,400
Do you love me?

8
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:28,310
I understand
your restlessness and loneliness,

9
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:31,590
as much as I understand myself.

10
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,150
To me, love...

11
00:02:35,890 --> 00:02:37,030
isn't that difficult.

12
00:02:37,363 --> 00:02:38,216
It's just like...

13
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,360
Like what?

14
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:00,500
Dad.

15
00:03:00,970 --> 00:03:01,850
Mum.

16
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:04,600
Meng Zhen. Let's eat.

17
00:03:05,970 --> 00:03:07,120
I want to drink it.

18
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:09,440
Xiao Jun, eat up.

19
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:10,910
It's okay, he can have it.

20
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:13,600
It helps in digestion.

21
00:03:17,850 --> 00:03:18,730
Here.

22
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:20,370
Take it.

23
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:21,990
Try it to see if it's delicious.

24
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:25,510
I don't like eggplant.

25
00:03:25,850 --> 00:03:28,190
Xiao Jun, don't be rude.

26
00:03:28,930 --> 00:03:30,336
Zhang Yi Chi loves eggplant.

27
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:31,576
When I was hospitalised,

28
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:33,760
I saw him ordering
braised eggplant with rice.

29
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:37,630
Xiao Jun has good memories.

30
00:03:38,530 --> 00:03:40,150
It's not good to be a picky eater.

31
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:47,006
Here, let's dig in.

32
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:48,770
-Here.
-Okay.

33
00:03:50,050 --> 00:03:50,930
Here.

34
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:53,390
Okay.

35
00:03:54,180 --> 00:03:55,110
Well...

36
00:03:55,650 --> 00:03:56,530
Meng Zhen.

37
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:59,360
What do you do for a living?

38
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:02,820
I own a bookstore.

39
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:07,030
I also sell clothes that I design
on my own and some stationary.

40
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:11,160
You're self-employed.

41
00:04:15,890 --> 00:04:18,280
Back in the university,
which course did you major in?

42
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:21,006
I majored in Dramatic Literature.

43
00:04:21,090 --> 00:04:22,326
After graduating from the university,

44
00:04:22,410 --> 00:04:24,993
I went back to my hometown and joined
an opera troupe as a screenwriter.

45
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:27,286
I think it's fate.

46
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:28,790
I decided to stay in Ningjiang.

47
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:30,909
In the end, I set up the bookstore...

48
00:04:32,650 --> 00:04:34,240
and met my late husband.

49
00:04:34,409 --> 00:04:35,590
Your late husband?

50
00:04:37,170 --> 00:04:38,390
He's a military officer.

51
00:04:39,010 --> 00:04:40,790
He sacrificed in a battle eight years ago.

52
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,220
It's not easy to be you.

53
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:47,040
It's all right.

54
00:04:51,570 --> 00:04:52,450
Dad.

55
00:04:53,090 --> 00:04:55,510
Meng Zhen is the most talented...

56
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,446
among my female friends.

57
00:04:57,530 --> 00:05:00,030
Furthermore,
she knows how to live a good life.

58
00:05:02,690 --> 00:05:04,280
I bet you live under stress.

59
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:07,480
Everyone lives under stress these days.

60
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:12,120
For example, in the hospital,
those residents who work under me...

61
00:05:12,890 --> 00:05:15,046
usually resign within three years.

62
00:05:15,130 --> 00:05:16,230
Do you know why?

63
00:05:16,410 --> 00:05:18,495
Their job is tiring and worse,
they don't make much from it.

64
00:05:18,580 --> 00:05:20,190
Their income is not as much
as self-employed.

65
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:22,880
If the job is so terrible,

66
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:25,990
why don't you change jobs
and become a bookseller too?

67
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,430
You don't say.

68
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,310
It's crossed my mind before.

69
00:05:32,530 --> 00:05:33,409
Meng Zhen.

70
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,350
Are you hiring?

71
00:05:39,650 --> 00:05:41,390
Stop joking.

72
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:42,558
You're a cardiac surgeon.

73
00:05:42,643 --> 00:05:44,056
Don't put yourself on a job
unworthy of your talents.

74
00:05:44,141 --> 00:05:45,350
What are you talking about?

75
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:48,470
To be frank, everyone can be
a master in their own special field.

76
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:51,600
There is neither lowliness
nor nobleness in careers.

77
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:55,270
Be it a doctor
or a self-employed bookstore owner,

78
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:57,910
I think it's just a job anyway.

79
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,200
Am I right, dad?

80
00:06:07,810 --> 00:06:09,960
Here. Try the braised eggplant.

81
00:06:10,553 --> 00:06:11,416
Try it.

82
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,380
Here.

83
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:13,736
It's your son's favourite.

84
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:15,240
Here, try it.

85
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,750
Mum, I need to use the washroom.

86
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,720
Sure, let me show you the way.

87
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:22,016
I can show him the way.

88
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:23,670
It's okay. I know the way.

89
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,440
Sit down.

90
00:06:31,569 --> 00:06:33,605
Even if you don't want
to date someone of the same profession,

91
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:35,840
you can find someone
from another profession.

92
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:38,950
She could be a banker, a teacher,
or a government servant.

93
00:06:39,409 --> 00:06:41,270
We have introduced so many ladies to you.

94
00:06:41,409 --> 00:06:42,830
Any of them is a good catch.

95
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:44,486
How aren't you fond of them?

96
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:45,640
Look at you.

97
00:06:46,045 --> 00:06:47,566
You're after a lady
who got married before.

98
00:06:47,650 --> 00:06:48,646
She has a son too.

99
00:06:48,730 --> 00:06:50,616
What's wrong with a lady
who got married before?

100
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,030
What's wrong with that?

101
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:54,670
Mum, what's wrong with you?

102
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,790
Are you here to mess things up?

103
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,180
Mum.

104
00:06:58,970 --> 00:07:00,496
-Have you washed your hands?
-Yes.

105
00:07:00,580 --> 00:07:01,460
Let's go.

106
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:02,970
Mum.

107
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:05,880
I shouldn't have come with you, right?

108
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:06,990
No.

109
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,686
Why do you think so?

110
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:11,950
I can feel that
the old lady doesn't like me.

111
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,150
What makes you feel so?

112
00:07:15,490 --> 00:07:16,803
She said that I'm not good.

113
00:07:19,570 --> 00:07:22,280
You've misunderstood.
She doesn't mean that.

114
00:07:23,650 --> 00:07:26,150
She thinks that it's not good
to be a picky eater.

115
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:29,366
Look, you're still young, right?
You're growing.

116
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:31,470
How do you grow up
if you are fussy about food?

117
00:07:31,890 --> 00:07:33,630
She said that out of concern.

118
00:07:34,380 --> 00:07:36,646
I criticise you at times too, right?

119
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:38,240
However, I'll always love you.

120
00:07:39,170 --> 00:07:40,200
Am I right?

121
00:07:41,370 --> 00:07:42,720
Stop thinking too much. Let's go.

122
00:07:43,409 --> 00:07:45,040
If only I was not born.

123
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:48,460
Xiao Jun.

124
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:50,670
Listen carefully.

125
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:54,870
To me, you're the most important.

126
00:07:56,060 --> 00:07:57,800
I don't mind losing everything...

127
00:07:59,610 --> 00:08:01,390
but I can't afford to lose you.

128
00:08:02,660 --> 00:08:03,550
Do you get it?

129
00:08:04,690 --> 00:08:05,570
Yes.

130
00:08:06,330 --> 00:08:07,210
That's great.

131
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:08,290
Be happy.

132
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:09,510
Be happy.

133
00:08:10,810 --> 00:08:11,690
Let's go.

134
00:08:13,340 --> 00:08:14,246
Listen.

135
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,550
For example, in the hospital,

136
00:08:16,210 --> 00:08:19,390
the best surgeon
is not necessarily the most popular.

137
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:23,830
The person who suits me the best
is not necessarily a catch.

138
00:08:24,370 --> 00:08:27,366
You're paranoid
because I don't have a girlfriend.

139
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,600
When I finally date someone,
you're being fussy.

140
00:08:30,530 --> 00:08:32,150
I'm already 38 years old.

141
00:08:32,610 --> 00:08:36,110
Of course. I'm not compromising
because I'm getting old.

142
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:39,046
That's because Meng Zhen is outstanding.
She's really outstanding.

143
00:08:39,130 --> 00:08:40,790
You haven't discovered that side of her.

144
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:43,360
It's destiny.

145
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:44,560
I accept my fate.

146
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:53,510
In that case,
you're ready to be a stepfather.

147
00:08:55,090 --> 00:08:57,350
Xiao Jun is a good boy.

148
00:08:58,690 --> 00:08:59,896
That's irrelevant.

149
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:03,160
Moving forward, if you marry his mum,

150
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:05,480
you'll have a son all of a sudden.

151
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:08,150
It's not about living together
for a short period of time.

152
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:11,030
You'll have to live together
day in and day out.

153
00:09:11,330 --> 00:09:14,070
It could be a few years
or a few decades.

154
00:09:15,090 --> 00:09:17,120
Both of you are not blood related.

155
00:09:17,930 --> 00:09:22,910
Are you sure you can be responsible
to him as a stepfather?

156
00:09:23,810 --> 00:09:24,690
Also,

157
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:27,720
moving forward,
you will have your own child.

158
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:29,393
You will have two children in total.

159
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,510
Are you sure when the time comes,

160
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:35,400
you can be fair to both of them?

161
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:39,430
Xiao Jun.

162
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,150
You're back.

163
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:57,200
Xiao Jun has to go to school tomorrow.
He can't stay up.

164
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:59,400
I'm bringing him home.
Enjoy the food.

165
00:10:00,730 --> 00:10:01,920
Let me escort you out.

166
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:03,526
It's okay. We can go back on our own.

167
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:04,456
Let's go.

168
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:05,440
Xiao Chi!

169
00:10:08,690 --> 00:10:10,190
I'm full.

170
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:11,260
You!

171
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,240
Meng Zhen.

172
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:20,640
Let me send you.

173
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:24,360
It's okay.
We can go back on our own.

174
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:27,406
By the way, I've transferred
the money for the present to you.

175
00:10:27,490 --> 00:10:29,520
Thank you for preparing
the present on behalf of me.

176
00:10:30,540 --> 00:10:31,750
What is going on?

177
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:34,416
Let's go. Let me send you.

178
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,390
It's okay.

179
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:38,710
It'll be difficult to drop the habit
once it becomes one.

180
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:42,350
Then, I'll just keep the habit.

181
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:49,070
When your dad asked you the question,
you hesitated, didn't you?

182
00:10:57,530 --> 00:10:59,120
I'm a mother with a son.

183
00:10:59,410 --> 00:11:01,456
Hence, I can understand
your parent's feelings.

184
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:04,080
They just want to protect their son
and give what's best to their son.

185
00:11:04,210 --> 00:11:05,790
It's understandable.

186
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:08,160
Therefore,
please understand my feelings too.

187
00:11:09,490 --> 00:11:10,750
As for our relationship,

188
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:12,880
please give it some thought.

189
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:15,670
Both of us should give it some thought.
What do you think?

190
00:11:22,090 --> 00:11:23,966
Xiao Jun, say goodbye to Yi Chi.

191
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:24,950
Goodbye.

192
00:11:26,010 --> 00:11:26,890
We're leaving.

193
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,150
Are you hungry?

194
00:11:57,780 --> 00:11:59,830
Here. It's time to eat.

195
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:04,580
Eat up.

196
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:11,550
What's wrong?

197
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,430
Give me a shave.
Didn't you complain that it's prickly?

198
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:18,830
Give you a shave?
Can't you do it on your own?

199
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,270
I can't do it.

200
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:21,726
Why?

201
00:12:21,810 --> 00:12:22,710
I'm injured.

202
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:24,960
Where did you hurt yourself?

203
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:26,230
It's over here.

204
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:28,870
Let me see.

205
00:12:32,490 --> 00:12:33,520
Is it painful?

206
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:37,110
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

207
00:12:38,210 --> 00:12:39,310
Give me a shave.

208
00:12:43,610 --> 00:12:44,560
Okay.

209
00:12:44,690 --> 00:12:45,710
I'll do it for you.

210
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:07,550
You're quite good at shaving.
Have you done it before?

211
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:10,260
For whom?

212
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:11,670
Zhuo Ran?

213
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:15,270
I did it for patients.

214
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:17,510
When I worked
at the general surgery department,

215
00:13:17,917 --> 00:13:20,126
I was in charge of skin preparation
before surgery was conducted.

216
00:13:20,210 --> 00:13:21,470
It lasted for a month.

217
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:26,120
Making you shave
is a waste of your talents.

218
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:32,430
Thank you, Liang Mu Ze.

219
00:13:33,330 --> 00:13:34,400
What for?

220
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:36,360
Thank you for carrying me back home.

221
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:38,240
I didn't know that
you've injured yourself.

222
00:13:39,490 --> 00:13:41,000
I chose to carry you on my back.

223
00:13:41,660 --> 00:13:43,030
I hit you too.

224
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:44,960
Is it painful?

225
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:46,110
Yes.

226
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:50,376
What should I do?
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

227
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:52,269
You've hit me anyway.
What's the point of telling you?

228
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:54,990
Well...

229
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:57,430
How should I make up to you?

230
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:00,136
You are already making up to me.

231
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,590
It would be better
if you could take it more seriously.

232
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:09,680
No matter what,
I still want to thank you.

233
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:12,376
If you didn't appear today,

234
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:14,080
I would be put through
a more awkward situation.

235
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:16,080
Are you sure you're only awkward today?

236
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:23,190
You can say whatever you want.

237
00:14:32,460 --> 00:14:33,680
It's done, Captain Liang.

238
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,000
Are you happy with it?

239
00:14:35,290 --> 00:14:37,200
Not bad, at least you didn't injure me.

240
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:43,600
Perhaps you're right.

241
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:46,560
There is nevertheless
a gap of eight years.

242
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:48,880
Many things have changed.

243
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:50,350
Example?

244
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:54,110
Zhuo Ran admitted
that he installed the tapping device.

245
00:14:55,410 --> 00:14:57,030
I knew it from the beginning.

246
00:14:58,130 --> 00:14:59,520
You knew it?

247
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:02,990
My understanding of Zhuo Ran
is beyond your imagination.

248
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:07,750
You won, Liang Mu Ze.

249
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:10,590
Like I said, I don't care about winning.

250
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:12,550
I care about the people.

251
00:15:23,740 --> 00:15:24,640
It's for you.

252
00:15:27,650 --> 00:15:29,406
What a cute keychain.

253
00:15:29,490 --> 00:15:30,510
Where did you get it?

254
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:31,910
I made it.

255
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:33,910
You?

256
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,670
You know how to make this?

257
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:37,160
Do you like it?

258
00:15:38,580 --> 00:15:40,480
I like anything that comes from you.

259
00:15:40,650 --> 00:15:42,646
If that's the case, keep it properly.

260
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:43,606
Don't lose it.

261
00:15:43,690 --> 00:15:44,670
Got it?

262
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:46,400
Sure.

263
00:15:49,530 --> 00:15:50,430
Xia Chu.

264
00:15:55,020 --> 00:15:58,590
The person who attempted to kidnap you
has been arrested by the police.

265
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:02,630
However, you have to be careful.
Stay vigilant.

266
00:16:04,140 --> 00:16:05,120
Especially...

267
00:16:06,220 --> 00:16:07,200
What?

268
00:16:08,570 --> 00:16:11,040
Don't meet up with Zhuo Ran alone.

269
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:12,720
It's for your own good.

270
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:19,350
Got it.

271
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:34,920
I instructed my secretary to get you
a set of lingerie based on your size.

272
00:16:35,290 --> 00:16:36,550
